The paper deals with processing SPARQL queries over a large RDF graph in a distributed environment, which involves techniques related to databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.Distributed), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical and experimental analysis of the proposed algorithms, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
